%N A392937 Square array T, read by ascending antidiagonals, where T(n,k) (n, k >= 1) denotes the smallest position at which a length‑n block of digits starting at position k reappears in the decimal expansion of Pi.
%C A392937 For n < 9 and k < 9, T(n,k) < 10^(n+1).
%e A392937 T(1,1) = A065593(1) = 10, because 10 is the smallest position at which a length‑1 block of digits starting at position 1, namely 3, reappears in the decimal expansion of Pi (A000796).
%e A392937 T(2,3) = 37, because 37 is the smallest position at which a length‑2 block of digits starting at position 3, namely 41, reappears in the decimal expansion of Pi (A000796).
